Jevic's revenue per terminal for 1996 was approximately $31.0 million. Description: Getting good kids into great colleges through personal mentoring and upcoming digital scalable services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: OUR MARKET Over 1,250,000 high school seniors apply to college every year. At least half of them write college application essays. Hundreds of thousands of college grads apply to graduate or professional programs annually. By 2025 there will be over a quarter of a billion people in post-secondary education worldwide. VALUE PROPOSITION Essays can make the difference in getting into college and winning financial aid. It’s an area of high need and high stress. We address problems for at least four distinct groups: --Students are often at a loss at how to write college essays; it is a daunting task for most of them; --Parents report that the essay causes the most stress and friction in the family in the college admissions process; --High schools, non-profits and college counselors have virtually no resources to help their students write effective essays; --College admissions offices struggle with poor essays that do not give them the information they need. PRODUCTS AND SERVICES For the past three years we have provided personal one-on-one mentoring to students locally (in person) and nationwide (through Skype and phone calls). We guide our students through a scalable, replicable four-stage process that consistently leads to enjoyable, personal, authentic and effective college essays. Our business model brings our process to the larger market through Essay Mentors Online. Just as TurboTax Online simulates the expertise of an accountant so people can do their taxes, Essay Mentors Online simulates the expertise of our mentors so students can write great essays at an affordable price. As we expand into the full college admissions process, graduate degrees, and overseas programs, we will touch the lives of young people worldwide, helping put them on a path to more solid and exciting futures. We’ve developed to expert content and structure and are just waiting for investment to build MVP. A SOCIAL PURPOSE CORPORATION Access to a quality college education is one of the most important challenges we face today. Essay Mentors partners with schools and non-profits to make our programs available to students from at-risk, disadvantaged or underserved groups. As a Washington State Social Purpose Corporation (similar to Benefit Corporations in other states) making the world a better place is built into our DNA.

Description: Hitch is a crowdsourced delivery marketplace that allows Shippers to leverage available cargo space during a Travelers commute.
Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: At it's core, Hitch is about challenging the shipping/delivery industry...the status quo if you will. There's a 100% chance someone is already headed in the direction your item needs to go. Hitch is about tapping into that people power to give you choices.   Founded by a leadership team that includes veterans in Transportation, Finance, Marketing and Technology, the Hitch team believed that same day delivery services were an unmet need for todays consumer.   Barriers to entry such as cost and timeliness are no longer an issue using the Hitch app.  Consumers have the choice to be Shippers, Travelers or both.  When it comes right down to it, that's what Hitch is really all about; Every Day Shipping...Everyday People.
